<TITLE> Truck hits train in Australia, kills 6 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 SYDNEY, June 5 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Six people were killed and 12 serious injured on Tuesday when a semi-trailer truck and passenger train collided in the southern Australian state of Victoria, police said. Another 40 passengers suffered minor injuries in the collision near the rural town of Swan Hill in northwest Victoria, a police spokeswoman told Reuters. "We have had a semi-trailer truck hit a passenger train. The train has derailed. We do not know how many carriages," she said. Emergency officials said the injured were being treated and assessed at the scene of the crash, which was reportedly a level railroad crossing. "We have air ambulances flying in and out," said Robert Jarman, chief of nearby Kerang Hospital. "We have just received the first patient. He has facial injuries and is serious and not in a stable condition.
